---
import Page from "../layouts/Page.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import TerminalPaper from "../components/TerminalPaper.astro";
import LiveHub from "../components/LiveHub.astro";
import HubBrowse from "../components/HubBrowse.astro";
import Chip from "../components/Chip.astro";
import { HUB_URL, REPO_URL, BBB, VERSION, BORROWED_LIGHT_URL } from "../config";

const HUB_HOST = HUB_URL.replace(/^https?:\/\//, "");
---
<Page
  title="Vela · scientific frontier state, signed and replayable"
  description="A git-native protocol for replayable scientific frontier state. Findings with conditions, signed by their reviewers, distributed by signed manifest."
  active="home"
  eyebrow="00 · Vela"
  pageTitle="Vela"
  subtitle="A git-native protocol for replayable scientific frontier state."
>
  <div slot="aside">
    <a href={REPO_URL} class="aside-link">github</a>
    <span>·</span>
    <a href={HUB_URL} class="aside-link">hub</a>
    <span>·</span>
    <Chip variant="live" label={`v${VERSION}`} />
  </div>

  <p class="t-lead">
    Vela turns a folder of papers into a bounded, reviewable state — claims with their evidence, conditions, confidence, and provenance — that a scientist or an agent can correct, replay, and sign.
  </p>

  <p class="t-lead" style="font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink-2);">
    A finding has a content-addressed id. A frontier has a content-addressed id. Two implementations agree byte-for-byte. The hub is dumb transport; clients verify locally. The signature is the bind.
  </p>

  <aside class="why-card">
    <div class="why-card__eyebrow">Why this exists</div>
    <blockquote class="why-card__quote">
      <p>Whoever owns the substrate decides what the next generation of agents inherits as fact. That choice is being made now, mostly without anyone noticing. If the substrate defaults to closed, proprietary document silos with AI wrappers on top, that is what science inherits. What calcifies first becomes hardest to replace.</p>
      <footer>
        <a href={`${BORROWED_LIGHT_URL}/`} rel="noopener">— <em>Constellations of Borrowed Light</em></a>
      </footer>
    </blockquote>
    <p class="why-card__bridge">
      The long-form argument lives at <a class="inline-link" href={BORROWED_LIGHT_URL} rel="noopener">borrowedlight.org</a>. This page is the working substrate that argument calls for: open Rust, open hub, open keys, open protocol. Read the essay if you're deciding whether the problem is real; read on if you've already decided and want to publish.
    </p>
  </aside>

  <Section num="§1" title="Browse the live hub" aside={`public hub · ${HUB_HOST}`}>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 64ch; margin: 0 0 12px;">
      Every entry below is a signed manifest pointing at a frontier file the publisher hosts elsewhere. Click any row to open it in the Workbench. {BBB.name} republishes weekly from CI; the others are one-shot publications.
    </p>
    <LiveHub />
    <HubBrowse />
    <TerminalPaper title="list and pull from the command line">
      <span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela registry list</span> <span class="tm-flag">--from</span> {HUB_URL}/entries
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela registry pull</span> &lt;vfr_id&gt; <span class="tm-flag">--from</span> {HUB_URL}/entries <span class="tm-flag">--out</span> ./pulled.json
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela registry pull</span> &lt;vfr_id&gt; <span class="tm-flag">--from</span> {HUB_URL}/entries <span class="tm-flag">--transitive</span> <span class="tm-flag">--out</span> ./out  <span class="tm-ps"># walks cross-frontier deps</span>
    </TerminalPaper>
  </Section>

  <Section num="§2" title="Read the essay" aside="why state · what state · what composes">
    <a class="essay-card" href="/essays/science-needs-state">
      <span class="eyebrow">Essay · 2026-04-25</span>
      <h3 class="title">Science Needs State</h3>
      <p class="blurb">
        Two papers contradict each other. A foundation officer makes a decision in the shower the next morning, and the reasoning evaporates. The thing science is missing is state. Here is the smallest substrate that holds.
      </p>
      <span class="readmore">Read →</span>
    </a>
  </Section>

  <Section num="§3" title="Install and publish" aside="one binary · five commands">
    <div class="quickstart">
      <TerminalPaper title="install">
        <span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">git clone</span> {REPO_URL}
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">cd</span> vela <span class="tm-ps">&&</span> <span class="tm-cmd">cargo build</span> <span class="tm-flag">--release</span>
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">./target/release/vela</span> <span class="tm-flag">--version</span>
      </TerminalPaper>
      <TerminalPaper title="publish your own frontier">
        <span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela frontier new</span> ./frontier.json <span class="tm-flag">--name</span> "Your bounded question"
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela finding add</span> ./frontier.json <span class="tm-flag">--assertion</span> "..." <span class="tm-flag">--author</span> reviewer:you <span class="tm-flag">--apply</span>
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela sign generate-keypair</span> <span class="tm-flag">--out</span> keys
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela actor add</span> ./frontier.json reviewer:you <span class="tm-flag">--pubkey</span> "$(cat keys/public.key)"
<span class="tm-ps">$</span> <span class="tm-cmd">vela registry publish</span> ./frontier.json <span class="tm-flag">--owner</span> reviewer:you <span class="tm-flag">--key</span> keys/private.key <span class="tm-flag">--locator</span> &lt;url&gt; <span class="tm-flag">--to</span> {HUB_URL}
      </TerminalPaper>
    </div>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 15px; color: var(--ink-2); margin: 12px 0 0;">
      Walk-through with cross-frontier composition and the BBB-style CI pattern at <a class="inline-link" href="/publish">/publish</a>.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section num="§4" title="Six nouns" aside="content-addressed · canonical-JSON · Ed25519">
    <ul class="nouns">
      <li>
        <span class="k">finding</span>
        <span class="d">A typed assertion: what was observed, in what conditions, with what evidence, by whom, citing what. Has a content-addressed <code>vf_…</code> id.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">frontier</span>
        <span class="d">A bounded scope holding findings, links, actors, and the event log that records every change. Has a content-addressed <code>vfr_…</code> id.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">proposal</span>
        <span class="d">A signed change-request: revise, retract, contest, annotate. Becomes a canonical event when reviewed and accepted.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">event</span>
        <span class="d">An immutable record in the log. Replay events on a fresh frontier and you reconstruct state byte-identically.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">registry</span>
        <span class="d">A directory of signed manifests pointing at frontier publications. Anyone can publish; clients verify on read.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="k">proof packet</span>
        <span class="d">A sealed snapshot another party can re-verify offline. The snapshot hash, the event-log hash, and the signatures are the audit.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section num="§5" title="Read the docs" aside="five-doc tour">
    <div class="card-grid">
      <a class="card" href="/docs/protocol">
        <span class="eyebrow">01 · protocol</span>
        <h3 class="title">Protocol</h3>
        <p class="blurb">The on-disk shape: findings, frontiers, events, signatures.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/docs/first-frontier">
        <span class="eyebrow">02 · first frontier</span>
        <h3 class="title">Your first frontier</h3>
        <p class="blurb">Compile a folder of papers into reviewable state in 10 minutes.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/docs/registry">
        <span class="eyebrow">03 · registry</span>
        <h3 class="title">Registry</h3>
        <p class="blurb">Verifiable distribution. Sign a manifest; anyone can pull and verify.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/docs/hub">
        <span class="eyebrow">04 · hub</span>
        <h3 class="title">Hub</h3>
        <p class="blurb">HTTP transport over the registry. The public hub at <code>{HUB_HOST}</code>.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="card" href="/docs/python">
        <span class="eyebrow">05 · python</span>
        <h3 class="title">Python SDK</h3>
        <p class="blurb">Programmatic access to a Vela frontier from Python.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Page>

<style>
  .aside-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .aside-link:hover { color: var(--ink-0); }
  div[slot="aside"] {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .why-card {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--signal);
    padding: 18px 24px 20px;
    margin: 8px 0 32px;
    background: var(--paper-1);
  }
  .why-card__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .why-card__quote {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    padding: 0;
    border: 0;
  }
  .why-card__quote p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-1);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .why-card__quote footer {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .why-card__quote footer a {
    color: var(--ink-3);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .why-card__quote footer a:hover { color: var(--signal); }
  .why-card__bridge {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 12px 0 0;
    padding-top: 12px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
  }

  .essay-card {
    display: block;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
    padding: 22px 26px;
    background: var(--paper-0);
    transition: border-color var(--dur-1) var(--ease), background var(--dur-1) var(--ease);
  }
  .essay-card:hover { border-color: var(--rule-ink); background: var(--paper-1); }
  .essay-card .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-tick);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    display: block;
  }
  .essay-card .title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 26px;
    color: var(--ink-0);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .essay-card .blurb {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .essay-card .readmore {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .essay-card:hover .readmore { color: var(--signal); }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--signal);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
  }

  .nouns {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-2);
  }
  .nouns li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    padding: 14px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-1);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .nouns li .k {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .nouns li .d {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-1);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .nouns li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 4px; }
  }
</style>
